In engraving large shadow at the side of the head, missing in the Brussels painting bought 1952. Measurements of the panel 12,6 x 9,2 cm. The photograph is a little enlarged. Cf. T.102 for eyes. Comparison with Vorsterman's print shows that the panel was not only cut down at the sides, but [onderstreept] 'also at top and bottom', so that head is almost in centre. Thus the picture was originally much larger. Then there was much more room for signature. Original diameter c. 18 cm. The etching has the same frame as the resurrection.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>1 zw/w foto met stempel ACL. In engraving large shadow at the side of the head, missing in the Brussels painting bought 1952. Measurements of the panel 12,6 x 9,2 cm. The photograph is a little enlarged. Cf. T.102 for eyes. Comparison with Vorsterman's print shows that the panel was not only cut down at the sides, but [onderstreept] 'also at top and bottom', so that head is almost in centre. Thus the picture was originally much larger. Then there was much more room for signature. Original diameter c. 18 cm. The etching has the same frame as the resurrection.</content>
<keyword>Brussel, Koninklijke Musea voor Schone Kunsten van België</keyword>
